                            <div class="accordion-content-inner">
                                <p>Goods and Services Tax (GST) is an indirect tax used in India on the supply of goods and services. It is a comprehensive, multi-stage, destination-based tax levied on every value addition. GST replaced multiple indirect taxes, simplifying the tax structure and promoting a common national market. It is crucial for businesses with a turnover exceeding specified limits to register under GST and file regular returns.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
