                            What is TDS and how does it work?
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
                        </button>
                        <div class="accordion-content">
                            <div class="accordion-content-inner">
                                 <p>Tax Deducted at Source (TDS) is a system where tax is deducted by a person (deductor) at the time of making certain payments (like salaries, rent, professional fees, etc.) to another person (deductee). The deducted tax is then remitted to the government. The purpose of TDS is to collect tax at the very source of income. The deductee receives a TDS certificate, which can be used to claim credit for the tax deducted when filing their income tax return.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
